description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gate 23 is the brand new location for Pinderfields Hospital discharge lounge, situated on C floor, we have 8 beds (we can flex to 11) and 6 chairs for seated patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our current staffing model is 2 RGNs and 2 HCAs days and 1 RGN and 1 HCA night shift.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to reconfiguration we have the exciting opportunity for 0.6 WTE (23 hours) band 6 vacancy, this will be predominately days, however you may be asked to do the occasional night shift&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The discharge lounge has a fast turnover of patients throughout the day/night, we accommodate patients from ED, surgery and medicine. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We ensure that the patients are discharged to their intended destination as smoothly as possible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We discharge to varied destinations- rehabilitation, step down hospital at DDH, back to care homes and to patients own homes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal client does not necessarily have to have a lot of discharge experience but would have ideally been qualified at least 2 years as they will be they will taking on the role of leadership within the team alongside the ward manager and 2 other band 6s.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a band 6 role this would entail roster management, sickness management, staff management, staff support, datix management, complaints, role in correct record keeping etc you would also be expected to be one of the leaders within the lounge and take on the responsibilities of the band 7 when she is unavailable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This would be an ideal opportunity for someone looking for change in a new and welcoming environment, who likes the challenge of fast turnover of patients whilst delivering the highest standards of care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
